sentences: James Edward Winston Langwith (20 April 1945 – 26 September 2020), known professionally as Jimmy Winston, was an English musician and actor.
Winston had apparently previously worked under the stage name James Moody.
His acting credits include the 1968 stage musical Hair and the 1972 Doctor Who serial Day of the Daleks.

In early 1965, Winston, along with his acquaintance Steve Marriott, formed Small Faces with Ronnie Lane and Kenney Jones.
The band released their debut single "Whatcha Gonna Do About It" later that year, peaking at number 14.
The group including Winston performed the song in Dateline Diamonds (1965).
Winston died on 26 September 2020, at the age of 75.
